From d0dc0dbbdba97850c3bcf77e65042155dc1d8f6d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dan on Selwyn <dan@awto.au>
Date: Thu, 16 Jul 2026 12:25:04 +1000
Subject: [PATCH] lib: translate base64, win_minmax to Rust (linux-rs TUs
 12-13)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

base64: the C recursive-macro reverse tables become a const fn computing
identical tables at compile time; sign-extension semantics of the s8
lookups preserved (invalid chars surface as negative val); unsigned-mask
comparisons kept via u32 casts. win_minmax: Nichols windowed min/max;
minmax_reset is a header static-inline invisible to bindgen —
reimplemented verbatim (new rule pattern); timestamp arithmetic uses
wrapping_sub as C unsigned subtraction requires.

Both integrated via dev.py integrate (Makefile patcher now handles
backslash-continuation lines and lib-y rules). Symbols verified in
System.map from the Rust objects; full regression boot green.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 lib/Makefile                    |  18 +++-
 lib/base64_rs.rs                | 179 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 lib/win_minmax_rs.rs            | 110 ++++++++++++++++++++
 rust/bindings/bindings_helper.h |   2 +
 4 files changed, 307 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)
 create mode 100644 lib/base64_rs.rs
 create mode 100644 lib/win_minmax_rs.rs

